                <a name="Instruction-about"></a>
                <h4> About</h4>
                <p>
                    The aim of the app is to provide a quick simple and efficient way of generating PO’s.
                    Using this application, a user can generate a Purchase order and email that order to a recipient.
                    All PO’s generated stored in a database for future reference.
                    <br /><br />
                    The app has been constructed to work across a range of devices Mob, tablets,
                    laptop and desktop computers able to run modern browsers.
                    If the device has a live connection to the internet whatever the location a PO can be created and sent.
                    <br />
                    This app currently sits on the Microsoft Azure platform.
                    <br /> <br />
                    To start generating PO’s a user needs a valid email address and register an account.
                </p>

                <a name="Instruction-top"></a>
                <h2>Instructions</h2>
                <a name="Instruction-CreateAccount"></a>
                <h4>Create an account</h4>
                <p>
                    Create an account
                    On the menu bar, top right click on register. The form below will appear
                </p>
                <div class="ImageContainer">
                    <img class="Image" src="~/Images/Register.JPG" />
                </div>
                <p>
                    Enter your details and click on Register. <br />

                    A confirmation email will be sent out asking you to confirm your account.  Please allow a short period of time
                    Then check your email, Open the email and click on the confirmation request. That will open the web site in a
                    browser and activate your account.  You can now login and begin creating PO’s.
                    <br />

                </p>
                <a name="Instruction-CreatePO"></a>
                <h4>  Create a Purchase Order </h4>
                <p></p>
                <p>
                    On the menu bar click on Purchase Order.  If you have not logged on the logon screen will appear,
                    enter your logon details and the following screen will appear. It will display a list of
                    the previously created PO's if there are any.  <br />
                    The display will adapt to the screen of the device you are using. The image below is taken from a browser
                    on a laptop. <br />
                    Note the text in blue indicates action links. Which if you click on or touch activates a process. eg
                    to sort a column press or click on "(---)" the column will be sorted andsort order displayed. Or if a PO number the PO will be displayed.
                <p />
                <div class="ImageContainer">
                    <img class="Image" src="~/Images/PurchaseOrder.JPG" />
                </div>
                <p>
                    Press Purchase Order then on the following screen press Create New Purchase order.  This
                    will present you with an empty Purchase Order form.
                </p>
                <div class="ImageContainer"> <img class="Image" src="~/Images/RaiseNewPO.JPG" /></div>
                <p>
                    The app will generate a code for the PO displayed in the Code field.
                    The date and time the PO was created displayed in the Date Raised field and status of the PO in the Status field.
                    A status of open means the PO is open for modifications.

                    The form consists of information fields you can edit and dropdown lists.
                    To add an item to a dropdown list, click on the dropdown
                    select “New  ******” a form will appear where you can enter the new option.
                    That option will be stored in the database and be available for future use.
                    <br /> <br />
                    The fields you need to enter are : <br /><br />
                    Budget Code (A dropdown): select from list or enter new code. <br /><br />

                    Date Required : Information field informing the recipient when you want\need the Items<br /><br />
                    Note : Additional  information  you feel necessary to add to the PO.<br /><br />

                    To (A dropdown) :  the organisation you want to send the PO to.  This will contain the email the PO will be sent to. <br /><br />
                    Pick from the list or enter a new organisation.<br /><br />
                    DeliverTo (A dropdown) :  the place you want the Items delivered.<br /><br />
                    InvoiceTo(A dropdown) :  the place the suppliers invoice is to be sent to.<br /><br />
                    Add Item to the PO. (A dropdown):  to add an Item to the PO Pick one from the dropdown or
                    select “New Item”. <br />If you select an Item it will appear on the PO where you can Change the quantity and price.  If you select new Item, you will be presented with a form where you can enter the item details. These will be stored in the database for future use and added to the
                    Current PO.
                    <br /><br />
                    Press save to Database to save the PO to the database.  It will be stored in the database and be available for modification until emailed to the recipient.
                    On emailing the Status of the PO will be sent.
                </p>
                <a name="Instruction-ViewEditPO"></a>
                <h4>  View \ Edit a Purchase Order </h4>
                <p>
                    On the menu bar click on Purchase Order. On the list of PO's click on the  PO Code you want to Edit \ View.
                    <br />
                    A status of "Open" the PO can be modified, "Sent" it can only be viewed.
                    <br>
                    The From displayed is the same as "Register a New PO" except the title is now "Edit Purchase Order" and some field have data from the previous
                    session.
                </p>
                <a name="Instruction-Organisation"></a>
                <h4> Organisation </h4>
                <p>
                    In the app an Organisation is the Name, Contact details (name and email) and address of an organisation. The email being esential
                    as the app will use that as the destination for the Purchase order.
                </p>
                <a name="Instruction-OrganisationRegister"></a>
                <h4> Register a new Organisation </h4>

                <p>
                    There are 2 ways to register a Organisation. <br />
                    1. on a PO form select new Organisation from a "To","Deliver to","Invoice to" drop drom list.
                    A pop up form shown below will appear into which you can enter the details. Press Save the organisation will be registered and
                    added to the dropdowns.
                <p />

                <div class="ImageContainer">
                    <img  class="Image" src="~/Images/OrganisationRegisterForm1.JPG" />
                </div>
                <p>
                    2. Select Organisations on the main menu then Create new. The form shown below will appear.
                <p />
                <div class="ImageContainer">
                    <img class="Image" src="~/Images/OrganisationRegisterForm2.JPG" />
                </div>
                <p>
                    Fill in the form and press save, the organisation will be registered on the system.
                </p>


